# RELEASE — firewalld-tumbleweed-config

Version:  v1.0
Date:     2026-04-04
Platform: openSUSE Tumbleweed
firewalld: 1.x / nftables backend

---

## What's in this release

### Initial production configuration
- nftables backend — replaces deprecated iptables
- `DefaultZone=public` (DROP) — all unassigned interfaces fall into the strictest zone
- `LogDenied=all` — every dropped/rejected packet logged to journald → Loki
- `ReloadPolicy=INPUT:DROP,FORWARD:DROP,OUTPUT:DROP` — no exposure window during reload
- `IPv6_rpfilter=yes` + `RFC3964_IPv4=yes` — anti-spoofing

### Zones
- `public` (DROP, br0) — whitelist-only: HTTPS 443, DNS 53, DoT 853, DoH 8053, Squid 10000, QUIC, torrent, NordVPN
- `trusted` (ACCEPT, source 192.168.1.0/24) — monitoring stack: Prometheus 9091, Grafana 3000, Loki 3100, Alertmanager 9093, all exporters
- `libvirt` (ACCEPT + reject rule priority 32767) — KVM VMs: DNS, DHCP, SSH, Squid, HTTPS
- `libvirt-routed` — routed KVM network
- `docker` (ACCEPT) — Docker bridge

### Policies
- `libvirt-to-host` (REJECT) — VMs cannot reach host freely, only DNS/DHCP/SSH/TFTP/ICMP
- `libvirt-routed-in/out` (ACCEPT) — routed VM traffic to/from network
- `allow-host-ipv6` (CONTINUE) — NDP neighbour-solicitation, neighbour-advertisement, router-advertisement

### Lockdown whitelist
- D-Bus access restricted to: firewall-config, root (uid 0), NetworkManager_t (SELinux), virtd_t (SELinux)
